RM  18554323
RT  EsaC substrate for the ESAT-6 secretion pathway and its role in
RT  persistent infections of Staphylococcus aureus.
RA  Burts ML, DeDent AC, Missiakas DM;
RL  Mol Microbiol. 2008;69:736-746.
CC  This Genome Property describes the Firmicutes secretion system related
CC  to the well-described type VII secretion system of Actinobacteria such
CC  as Mycobacterium tuberculosis. In both systems, members of the WXG100
CC  (PF06013) are targets, and a homolog of EccC (models TIGR03924 and
CC  TIGR03925) is present. Otherwise, differences appear to be profound.
**  SAG_1039=PF06013, SAG_1038, ,,,SAG_1033=EccC. EssA is massively
**  divergent and more widespread than authors realize.
